pom.xml File

<build>
    <plugins>
        <!-- Other plugins like maven-compiler-plugin, maven-release-plugin, etc. -->
        
        <!-- Add the exec-maven-plugin to run Python tests -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
            <artifactId>exec-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>3.0.0</version>
            <executions>
                <execution>
                    <id>run-python-tests</id>
                    <phase>test</phase> <!-- Runs during the test phase -->
                    <goals>
                        <goal>exec</goal>
                    </goals>
                    <configuration>
                        <executable>bash</executable> <!-- Using bash to run multiple commands -->
                        <arguments>
                            <argument>-c</argument>
                            <argument>
                                source venv/bin/activate &amp;&amp; pytest unittests/ --junitxml=target/report.xml
                            </argument>
                        </arguments>
                    </configuration>
                </execution>
            </executions>
        </plugin>
        
        <!-- Your existing plugins for packaging and release -->
    </plugins>
</build>



Explanation:
exec-maven-plugin: This plugin allows you to execute custom shell commands during the Maven build.
phase: The test phase is when this execution will take place.
executable: Specifies that bash should be used to run the commands.
arguments: The commands to be executed:
source venv/bin/activate: Activates the Python virtual environment.
pytest unittests/ --junitxml=target/report.xml: Runs all tests in the unittests/ directory using pytest and generates a test report in target/report.xml.


